<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>2. Building In Resilience on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/</link><description>Recent content in 2. Building In Resilience on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>2.1 File Storage Configuration</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/2-1-configuration/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/2-1-configuration/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this exercise, we will update the &lt;code&gt;extensions:&lt;/code&gt; section of the &lt;code&gt;agent.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file. This section is part of the OpenTelemetry configuration YAML and defines optional components that enhance or modify the OpenTelemetry Collector’s behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While these components do not process telemetry data directly, they provide valuable capabilities and services to improve the Collector’s functionality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Info&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2.2 Setup environment for Resilience Testing</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/2-2-test-environment/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/2-2-test-environment/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Next, we will configure our environment to be ready for testing the &lt;strong&gt;File Storage&lt;/strong&gt; configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start the Gateway&lt;/strong&gt;: In the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;../otelcol --config&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;gateway.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start the Agent&lt;/strong&gt;: In the &lt;strong&gt;Agent terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;../otelcol --config&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;agent.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Send five test spans&lt;/strong&gt;: In the &lt;strong&gt;Loadgen terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;../loadgen -count &lt;span class="m"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both the &lt;strong&gt;Agent&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Gateway&lt;/strong&gt; should display debug logs, and the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway&lt;/strong&gt; should create a &lt;code&gt;./gateway-traces.out&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2.3 Simulate Failure</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/2-3-failure/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/2-3-failure/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;To assess the &lt;strong&gt;Agent&amp;rsquo;s&lt;/strong&gt; resilience, we&amp;rsquo;ll simulate a temporary &lt;strong&gt;Gateway&lt;/strong&gt; outage and observe how the &lt;strong&gt;Agent&lt;/strong&gt; handles it:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simulate a network failure&lt;/strong&gt;: In the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway terminal&lt;/strong&gt; stop the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway&lt;/strong&gt; with &lt;code&gt;Ctrl-C&lt;/code&gt; and wait until the gateway console shows that it has stopped. The &lt;strong&gt;Agent&lt;/strong&gt; will continue running, but it will not be able to send data to the gateway. The output in the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway terminal&lt;/strong&gt; should look similar to this:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2.4 Recovery</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/2-4-recovery/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/conf/1-advanced-collector/2-building-resilience/2-4-recovery/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this exercise, we’ll test how the &lt;strong&gt;OpenTelemetry Collector&lt;/strong&gt; recovers from a network outage by restarting the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway&lt;/strong&gt; collector. When the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway&lt;/strong&gt; becomes available again, the &lt;strong&gt;Agent&lt;/strong&gt; will resume sending data from its last check-pointed state, ensuring no data loss.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Restart the Gateway&lt;/strong&gt;: In the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;../otelcol --config&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;gateway.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
